# Slide authoring playbook

When this rule fires, you're editing a deck's `index.html`. Slides are
linear `<section>` blocks. **Always copy the closest existing slide that
matches the layout you want and edit its content.** Don't write a new
slide from scratch ÔÇö every existing slide is a working example with the
right chrome.

## Anatomy

```html
<section>
  <div class="slide">                   <!-- or .slide.dark -->
    <div class="chrome">
      <div class="brand-lockup">
        <img class="logo" src="brand/General Logos/Lockup Horizontal/PNG/LOCKUP_HORIZONTAL_2D_LIGHT.png" alt="Cursor">
      </div>
      <div class="eyebrow">Section name</div>
    </div>

    <!-- body -->

    <div class="footer">
      <span class="left">Your Org ┬Ě Session 00 ┬Ě Topic</span>
      <span>NN / MM</span>
    </div>
  </div>
  <aside class="notes">Speaker notes for the S key.</aside>
</section>
```

## Layout starters

### Title (dark cover)

Use for slide 1 and the closer. `.slide.dark` + `.cube-wm` watermark +
big `.title-xl` headline.

### Content + bullets

Standard body slide: `.title-l` headline, `.lede` subtitle,
`.accent-rule`, then content. See template slide 4 ("Three things changeÔÇŽ").

### Section divider (dark)

Use to break the deck into chapters. Big section number in `.mono` +
`.title-xl` heading. See template slide 3.

### Megastat

One enormous number + headline (240px digit). Use `.megastat` grid.
See template slide 5.

### Cards grid

Use `.row-3` or `.row-4` of `.card` blocks (with `.num` + `.name` +
`.desc`). See template slide 4 / slide 8.

### Code block

`.code` div with `.titlebar` (filename) + `<pre>` content. Use spans
`.k` (keyword), `.s` (string), `.c` (comment), `.h` (highlight).
See template slide 6.

### Comparison table

`.cmp` table with three columns: dimension / before / after. Pair with a
`.callout` below for the punchline. See template slide 7.

### Quote / pull-quote

Centered slide with a single big quote. See template slide 9.

### Closing (dark)

`.slide.dark` + huge "Thanks." + speaker contact + resource list. See
template slide 10.

## Adding a slide ÔÇö step by step

1. Decide position. Slides are linear; insert between two existing ones.
2. Copy the closest matching `<section>...</section>` block.
3. Edit content inside `.slide`. Leave `.chrome` and `.footer` untouched
   except for the eyebrow text and counter.
4. **Bump the footer counter** on the new slide AND every following
   slide. Update the `MM` total on every slide.
5. Add speaker notes inside `<aside class="notes">ÔÇŽ</aside>`.
6. Match the logo variant: `*_LIGHT.png` on `.slide`, `*_DARK.png` on
   `.slide.dark`.

